create

public static Float64Array create(ArrayBuffer buffer,
                                  int byteOffset)
Creates a new instance of the TypedArray using the given ArrayBuffer to read/write values from/to. The TypedArray is created using the byteOffset to specify the starting point (in bytes) of the TypedArray relative to the beginning of the underlying ArrayBuffer. The byte offset must match (multiple) the value length of this TypedArray. if the byteLength is not valid for the given ArrayBuffer, an exception is thrown

Parameters:
buffer - the underlying ArrayBuffer of the newly created TypedArray.
byteOffset - the offset relative to the beginning of the ArrayBuffer (multiple of the value length of this TypedArray)
Returns:
the newly created TypedArray.

create

public static Float64Array create(ArrayBuffer buffer,
                                  int byteOffset,
                                  int length)
Creates a new instance of the TypedArray using the given ArrayBuffer to read/write values from/to. The TypedArray is created using the byteOffset and length to specify the start and end (in bytes) of the TypedArray relative to the beginning of the underlying ArrayBuffer. The byte offset must match (multiple) the value length of this TypedArray. The length is in values of the type of the TypedArray if the byteLength or length is not valid for the given ArrayBuffer, an exception is thrown

Parameters:
buffer - the underlying ArrayBuffer of the newly created TypedArray.
byteOffset - the offset relative to the beginning of the ArrayBuffer (multiple of the value length of this TypedArray)
length - the length of the TypedArray in vales.
Returns:
the newly created TypedArray.
